The article discusses the passing of Abe Shinzo, the longest-serving Prime Minister in Japan's history. It highlights his dedication to serving the Japanese people and his strong relationship with the United States. Abe worked with American Presidents from both parties to strengthen the alliance between the two nations and promote a free and open Indo-Pacific. The article also mentions that Abe was engaged in democratic work at the time of his death. As a mark of respect, the President of the United States has ordered that the American flag be flown at half-staff at various locations, both domestically and internationally, until July 10, 2022. The article concludes with the signature of Joseph R. Biden Jr., the President of the United States.